John Major, Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher's Chancellor of the Exchequer and her 
chosen heir apparent, was elected Conservative Party leader today and will become prime 
minister. Major won 185 votes. Both his opponents, former Defense Secretary Heseltine 
and Foreign Secretary Hurd, with131 votes and 56 votes, respectively, conceded defeat. 
Queen Elizabeth II will summon Major and ask him to form a cabinet after Thatcher 
surrenders her seals of office at Buckingham Palace on Wednesday.

Major, 47, a former welfare recipient, was elected to Parliament in1979, was appointed 
foreign secretary in July 1989, and Chancellor of the Exchequer three months later.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d120"
