SUMMARIZER="J">

Prime Minister John Major won the general election a year ago, but today he is a deeply 
unpopular, unproven leader. His party is internally torn over the controversy that 
accompanied Britain's withdrawal of sterling from the European Monetary System and 
by a lingering deep recession that has alienated many traditional supporters in business.

Most industrialists are grateful that he won the election and he is appreciated for personal 
qualities that are favorably compared to those of his predecessor. Unlike the former prime 
minister, however, he is viewed as a weak leader, with little vision and no clearly 
articulated political conviction.</SUM> 

<SUM
DOCSET="d120"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="FT933-10917"
