DOCREF="FT942-6613"
SELECTOR="I"
SUMMARIZER="J">

A biography of Mrs. Norma Major claims that the Majors' favorite film was "Being 
There," a movie about a vacuous gardener, Chauncey, who becomes a candidate for the 
U.S. presidency. I heartily concur with their choice. John Major must appreciate the 
similarities between himself and Chauncey. Like Chauncey whose bromides seem to 
convey whatever people want to believe they heard, Major is a chameleon. For the pro-
Europeans, he says he wants Britain to be at the heart of Europe, but before an audience 
of Euro-sceptics he freely insults the European Commission. He fits in with prevailing 
circumstances, no matter how fluctuating.</SUM>
